page.title: 14Paul's East Stour Stroll.
page.content: Up Heavland Lane I noticed the old quarry was getting filled up with mud from the hole which the new sewerage works will be put in.The works foreman said the quarry will soon be a field again.As I went on up the track I saw two cornfields,one silage field and the rest of the fields were for hay. I went to Stour Close and there were nine bungalows. There were nineteen in Witch Close. The scrap yard was still a scrap yard. There is a weighbridge too. The White Horse Inn is now an Embassy School of Motoring. Opposite there is a well, in fenced off land marked 'Private'.
